						               													<description>Games and exercises for brain-fair training. Train playfully your pictorial imagination.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Erweitern Sie Ihr Potential durch Gehirn-gerechtes Training.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is a booklet from Vera F. Birkenbihl for training. Your partner on the way to a brain-right using your brain-potential. Also there are games to play. 1. Difference (for concentration) :  2. Play with a correspodence in cipher. 3. Undercover mit 36 cards like a memory game.The cards are open. 6 wooden small plates are to cover 6 cards. Each plate with another colour. You play with a dice with the six colours of the plates and have to say what picture is under the plate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Difference: is a placement game with 4 laying boards and 36 picture cards for 2-4 players. You have to lay down pictures on a board (with the same pictures). The pictures only have small differences. The first player has his cards stored calls stop. With the control film is controlled. For each correct card there is a point. Four rounds, so everyone plays with each panel. The points are added up. The player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Undercover: is a memory game with 36 cards, 6 wooden discs and a cube. The aim of the game is to remember which motifs of ancient cultures are covered under the individual colored wooden discs, then color cubes with the correct predictions to collect after roll a most picture cards. The wooden plate is then placed on another subject. The cards are open. 6 wooden small plates are to cover 6 cards. Each plate with another colour. You play with a dice with the six colours of the plates and have to say what picture is under the plate.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Another game of the Ravensburger Think Series, a brainteaser/mental exercise game-series. These games are good for mental training, e.g. in creativity, concentration, imagination, logic and so on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Designer of GEHIRNPOTENTIAL is Vera F. Birkenbiehl.&amp;#10;Designer of DIFFERENCE is Elisabeth Richter.&amp;#10;Designer of UNDERCOVER is Heinz Meister.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
